text: Sergeant First Class is a military rank in some militaries and other uniformed organizations around the world. It is typically a senior non-commissioned officer. ==United States Army== Sergeant First Class (SFC) is the seventh enlisted rank (E-7) in the U.S. Army. It is above Staff Sergeant and below Master Sergeant and First Sergeant. It is the first senior non-commissioned officer rank. ==References== ==Other websites== * U.S. Army Enlisted Rank Insignia - Criteria, Background, and Images Category:Military ranks
